WEBVTT

00:00.160 --> 00:03.980
Ooh, check this one out! "Here lies
Damien Marrow. A fishmonger.

00:04.019 --> 00:07.070
Always had a smile on his face."
Aw, that's nice!

00:07.080 --> 00:08.910
How many are you planning to read?

00:08.949 --> 00:11.800
I dunno.
Another 80... maybe?

00:11.849 --> 00:13.470
Why, are you not enjoying it?
No.

00:13.509 --> 00:16.660
Of course not. It's incredibly
boring and creepy.

00:16.699 --> 00:18.190
I've no idea why you
wanted to come here.

00:18.199 --> 00:20.612
- I find their lives... interesting.
- Why?

00:20.652 --> 00:24.652
They're dull as shit. I couldn't
just be some smiling fishmonger.

00:24.679 --> 00:27.045
Ah, it'd be OK. You'd eat well!

00:27.050 --> 00:28.725
I don't want "OK".

00:28.812 --> 00:30.500
I want fucking great.

00:30.579 --> 00:33.649
I want to sail through a storm
and ride a white deer

00:33.689 --> 00:36.039
and have sex in the graveyard.

00:38.200 --> 00:40.805
Yeah, er...
bit disrespectful though, isn't it?

00:40.865 --> 00:42.192
And chilly.

00:42.299 --> 00:46.340
You're too safe, Marcus. You may as
well just jump in the grave now.

00:46.393 --> 00:50.365
Er... OK, well, if it's naughty grave
sex you want, let's do it.

00:50.432 --> 00:52.149
Right now.
Yeah, right.

00:52.189 --> 00:54.340
You couldn't handle it.

00:54.545 --> 00:56.369
Mmm.

01:02.253 --> 01:03.604
I'm so sorry for your loss.

01:03.640 --> 01:05.745
Plebs S03E08
The Weatherist

01:05.780 --> 01:07.725
# When in Rome

01:07.745 --> 01:10.192
# Do as the Romans do

01:13.420 --> 01:15.219
# Far from home

01:15.552 --> 01:18.644
â™ª All I got is you â™ª

01:19.239 --> 01:21.049
How can anyone be "too safe"?

01:21.090 --> 01:23.090
That's like a toilet
being too clean.

01:23.129 --> 01:25.879
I think she's gonna dump me.
Whoa, no, you'll win her round.

01:25.920 --> 01:29.466
Just give the girl a bit of danger.
I am terrible at danger, though.

01:29.609 --> 01:31.552
Maybe I'll take her on a mini-break
to Tuscany.

01:31.585 --> 01:33.229
There are some fairly hazardous
hill walks.

01:33.246 --> 01:34.740
Yeah, that might not cut it, bro.

01:34.753 --> 01:37.280
So what do I do, buy her
a pet crocodile?

01:37.319 --> 01:39.310
Push her down a well?

01:41.353 --> 01:43.173
Holy Jove, God of Thunder.

01:43.240 --> 01:45.390
What?
There's a hottie in the office!

01:45.430 --> 01:48.299
Finally! I was beginning to think
it was company policy

01:48.340 --> 01:51.120
that female staff
had to be total gorgons.

01:51.206 --> 01:53.250
Ah! Apart from Flavia, of course!

01:53.289 --> 01:55.599
Oh... Yeah, but Flavia's
senior management

01:55.640 --> 01:57.870
so that comment obviously
doesn't include her.

01:57.909 --> 01:59.670
Hey! Hi, Flavia.

01:59.710 --> 02:02.192
A bold but unconvincing
recovery, Shredder.

02:02.219 --> 02:04.599
Yeah.
You've noticed Pandora, then?

02:04.609 --> 02:07.665
Pandora?! Oh, her over there! Yeah.

02:07.680 --> 02:09.633
I can see her now. Is she new, then?

02:09.673 --> 02:13.052
Indeed, she is. The board
are planning to fast-track her.

02:13.073 --> 02:14.659
As is Stylax, I expect.

02:14.699 --> 02:17.449
Well, she's been
selected for her intelligence

02:17.453 --> 02:19.932
and good judgement, so
I can't see that happening.

02:19.992 --> 02:20.979
Oh...

02:21.052 --> 02:23.550
Gawping over, back to work!

02:27.272 --> 02:30.612
It's a step down from the palace,
but it has a certain...

02:30.652 --> 02:32.000
gritty charm.

02:32.152 --> 02:33.939
Oh! Er... what's that?

02:33.973 --> 02:37.913
- And a shitty charm.
- Yes... what are the neighbours like?

02:38.105 --> 02:39.819
Grumio, what are you like?

02:40.173 --> 02:41.699
I'm all right.
He's "all right"!

02:41.700 --> 02:44.513
Oh, right.
Well, yes... that'll do.

02:44.545 --> 02:46.406
Good. Good.

02:46.460 --> 02:49.409
Grumio, this is your
new neighbour, Strabo.

02:49.425 --> 02:51.280
Play nice, won't you?

02:59.849 --> 03:02.485
Hey, Pandora, is it? I'm Stylax.

03:02.520 --> 03:05.445
That's great. If you've got a memo,
please just pop it in my inbox.

03:05.500 --> 03:06.693
Oh, no, I don't have one of them.

03:06.705 --> 03:08.286
Just thought I'd come over
for a chat.

03:08.325 --> 03:11.490
And that's super, Stylax,
but I am currently streamlining

03:11.500 --> 03:13.599
the company's internal
communications system

03:13.626 --> 03:16.586
and learning Greek.
So now really isn't the best time.

03:16.620 --> 03:19.349
How about tonight, then?
I could help you bed in here.

03:19.389 --> 03:22.819
And thanks so much, but I've already
had a full staff induction.

03:22.860 --> 03:25.413
Tomorrow, then?
Tomorrow's basket weaving,

03:25.445 --> 03:27.120
then I'm in a conference in Rimini.

03:27.159 --> 03:30.712
Week after's chocca...
How about... April?

03:30.765 --> 03:32.349
April this year?
Uh-huh.

03:32.389 --> 03:34.460
How's your diary looking?
I don't own a diary.

03:34.500 --> 03:36.810
Perfect. Well, ping me
a couple of dates

03:36.849 --> 03:38.840
and we'll find a window.

03:40.832 --> 03:42.605
So you're going to wait until April?

03:42.652 --> 03:46.346
April, schmapril. I'll find a window
before that, you know,

03:46.379 --> 03:48.925
- hoik it open and slither in.
- Oh, how romantic

03:48.973 --> 03:51.000
Oh, give us a hand for a second,
would you, lads?

03:51.066 --> 03:53.620
The landlord's only gone and talked
some other stupid sucker

03:53.646 --> 03:56.030
into moving in here.
Oh! Go landlord!

04:02.466 --> 04:05.365
Carefully, please, precious cargo.

04:05.419 --> 04:07.592
All right, this is Strabo.

04:07.645 --> 04:09.419
Me and the big man
are helping him move in.

04:09.460 --> 04:12.300
Right... cos it looks more like
you are eating his food.

04:12.340 --> 04:14.610
All part of the service.
Sorry about this.

04:14.650 --> 04:17.279
Oh, you spicy bugger!
What is it, G man?

04:17.593 --> 04:21.620
Indian food. They call it takeaway,
cos you can take it... away.

04:21.692 --> 04:25.009
You can eat in, as well.
Honestly, the things this guy knows.

04:25.050 --> 04:26.730
Oh, cool, you've got ants!

04:26.769 --> 04:30.245
They're for my work. I call them
my assist-ants.

04:30.293 --> 04:32.220
What do you do, transport leaves?

04:32.432 --> 04:35.199
No. I'm a weatherist.

04:35.273 --> 04:38.086
My ants react to tiny changes
in the atmosphere,

04:38.120 --> 04:40.340
which I use to create a forecast.

04:40.540 --> 04:42.353
I did it for the Emperor
until recently.

04:42.406 --> 04:45.786
Wicked, what's he like?
Shorter than he looks in statues.

04:46.540 --> 04:49.100
This one is called Mark Antony.

04:49.300 --> 04:51.490
He's my most trusted barometer.

04:51.946 --> 04:53.439
At least I think this is him.

04:53.540 --> 04:55.112
Go on, then, give us a prediction.

04:55.240 --> 04:59.779
Very well. I scribbled something
on a scrap of papyrus..?

05:00.012 --> 05:03.680
Ah, yes, that's the chap.

05:03.766 --> 05:06.959
"Tomorrow is overcast
with occasional sunshine."

05:07.000 --> 05:07.904
Classic.

05:07.939 --> 05:09.939
Wendsday, a small drama

05:10.180 --> 05:12.293
followed by heavy rain
in the afternoon."

05:12.305 --> 05:14.319
Sorry. Did you just say "tremor"?

05:14.365 --> 05:17.286
"Followed by heavy rain
in the afternoon." Yes.

05:17.332 --> 05:19.045
Tremor, as in earthquake?

05:19.079 --> 05:22.653
According to Mark Antony here, it's
more of a flutter than a tremor.

05:22.680 --> 05:25.579
Perfectly safe,
but people tend to panic

05:25.620 --> 05:27.529
when you start talking
about earthquakes.

05:27.545 --> 05:29.759
Thinking they are going to die
and whatnot!

05:30.105 --> 05:32.159
So best not to spread it around.

05:33.389 --> 05:35.230
Hmm?

05:37.980 --> 05:39.952
So... there's gonna be
an earthquake tomorrow.

05:40.052 --> 05:41.680
What?! How do you know?

05:41.706 --> 05:44.159
I have it on the highest authority.
Oh, no.

05:44.199 --> 05:46.189
Please don't tell me
you've found God!

05:46.230 --> 05:47.959
Pass me some of those grapes
will you?

05:48.079 --> 05:50.745
Not God, my new neighbour.
He's a weatherist.

05:50.773 --> 05:53.129
Excuse-moi, he's a what?
A weatherist.

05:53.220 --> 05:55.360
A scientist of weather.
He used to work for the Emporer.

05:55.406 --> 05:57.870
He's legit, I promise.
Are you serious?

05:57.909 --> 05:59.759
An earthquake, here in Rome?

05:59.773 --> 06:02.540
Yeah, and maybe don't tell anyone,
might cause a bit of panic.

06:02.579 --> 06:03.552
So, what are we going to do?

06:03.692 --> 06:07.160
I guess, get some supplies in.
Drink whatever it is you're making

06:07.199 --> 06:10.870
and just embrace the danger...
and of course... each other.

06:10.910 --> 06:12.300
Is it going to be a big one?

06:12.326 --> 06:14.733
Well, he can't say for sure.
Because that would be amazing!

06:14.853 --> 06:18.329
Pretty big. Yeah, a bloody whopper.
Properly dangerous.

06:21.452 --> 06:23.110
I knew you'd win her round.

06:23.149 --> 06:26.060
It was mainly thanks to our
weird new neighbour and his ants.

06:26.100 --> 06:27.206
They're the real heroes.

06:27.240 --> 06:29.192
But, what about when the earthquake
never happens?

06:29.252 --> 06:32.072
I guess, as your girlfriend
she's used to disappointment!

06:32.372 --> 06:34.033
Oh, yeah, she's gonna be
really gutted

06:34.066 --> 06:35.612
she's not under a pile of rubble.

06:35.646 --> 06:38.180
It's all about the build up.
That's the sexy bit.

06:38.220 --> 06:40.480
That's why people bang each other
on sinking ships and stuff.

06:40.490 --> 06:42.620
Of course they don't,
it would be far too wobbly.

06:42.659 --> 06:46.733
When faced with death, people just
dump everything and hump anything.

06:47.586 --> 06:49.560
In fact... ooh!

06:49.673 --> 06:51.793
Where are you going?
Is this to do with humping?

06:51.840 --> 06:52.858
Oh, he's had a humping idea.

06:52.858 --> 06:54.372
- Tell me what it is?
- No.

06:54.766 --> 06:56.872
Bad friend! Bad person!

07:01.980 --> 07:03.120
Mmm.

07:04.720 --> 07:06.269
Here, you missed a bit.

07:07.326 --> 07:08.300
Ta.

07:10.279 --> 07:11.379
How was your meal, sirs?

07:11.406 --> 07:13.413
Cracking, thanks. Real spicy.

07:13.459 --> 07:14.680
Not too spicy, I hope?

07:14.713 --> 07:16.612
Nah, nah, nah. Nice and spicy.

07:16.639 --> 07:19.050
I tell you what, grab us two more
yellow currys, would you?

07:19.089 --> 07:19.959
Coming right up, sirs.

07:19.992 --> 07:22.860
A-a-actually, what's that red curry
they're eating over there?

07:23.019 --> 07:26.786
That is a speciality of the house.
Very, very spicy.

07:27.480 --> 07:29.865
- Oh! Give us that one this time, please.
- Good call.

07:29.920 --> 07:32.685
Oh, no, I'm sorry, but the red curry
is only for regulars.

07:32.759 --> 07:33.653
What?! Why?

07:33.706 --> 07:37.459
It's for your own safety, sir.
It requires a sturdy constitution.

07:37.505 --> 07:39.452
Sturdy constitution?
You're talking to a man

07:39.485 --> 07:41.100
who'll quite happily
eat out of a bin.

07:41.139 --> 07:43.370
And it's an honour to have you
dining with us, sir,

07:43.409 --> 07:45.040
but it will be the yellow curry.

07:45.439 --> 07:47.372
- Red curry.
- Yellow curry.

07:47.439 --> 07:49.590
- Yellow curry.
- Re-

07:50.233 --> 07:52.766
I'll send some
complimentary papadums.

07:59.600 --> 08:00.470
Salve, Pandora.

08:00.509 --> 08:03.220
Hi, Stylax. No time
for chit-chat, I'm afraid.

08:03.240 --> 08:06.365
I've got to action all of these
memos before today's budget meeting.

08:06.386 --> 08:08.985
Very much looking forward
to touching base in April, though.

08:09.052 --> 08:11.040
Oh, no, no. This isn't chit-chat,
this is work.

08:11.079 --> 08:12.485
I've got a work memo for you.

08:12.545 --> 08:14.629
Ah, OK, what am I filing it under?

08:14.670 --> 08:17.579
Er... I guess it's social, with a
hint of health and safety too.

08:17.872 --> 08:20.266
Well, let's hear it
and I'll make a call.

08:21.180 --> 08:25.293
All members of staff are cordially
invited to the copy room

08:25.326 --> 08:28.213
tomorrow afternoon...
- Yeah. That's definitely social.

08:28.245 --> 08:29.620
..cos there's gonna be
an earthquake.

08:29.685 --> 08:32.625
Oh! Wow! Gosh! I see.

08:32.799 --> 08:34.659
That is more health and safety now.
Yeah.

08:34.700 --> 08:37.250
Come and hunker down...
"Hunker down..."

08:37.289 --> 08:39.893
..in a safe, but fun, environment.

08:40.000 --> 08:42.639
Wear loose clothing.

08:42.852 --> 08:44.773
I'll get that off right away.
Great.

08:44.799 --> 08:46.779
Oh, and of course, do make sure
you come along.

08:46.820 --> 08:48.753
Erm... that's going
to be tough, Stylax,

08:48.779 --> 08:50.806
because I'm really getting slammed
here with work.

08:50.879 --> 08:53.480
Bring it with you. Treat my desk
as a hot desk.

08:53.519 --> 08:56.110
Is it a hot desk?
It would be if you were at it.

08:56.149 --> 08:58.149
Huh?

09:01.365 --> 09:03.090
Just get on the cart, Delphine.

09:03.129 --> 09:04.919
No, I'm not going anywhere.

09:04.960 --> 09:06.206
Hey, everything all right?

09:06.232 --> 09:07.913
Can you talk to her, please?

09:07.926 --> 09:11.820
She's refusing to leave and there's
gonna be a bloody big earthquake!

09:14.346 --> 09:17.725
I did say not to tell anyone.
I only told Maya...

09:19.046 --> 09:20.710
..and the other guys on the cart...

09:20.750 --> 09:22.750
Delphine?
..and Gregory.

09:22.789 --> 09:24.299
Ah, you told your ex!

09:29.480 --> 09:32.245
I am not on my own,
I am with Marcus.

09:32.312 --> 09:35.860
Marcus? This guy, Marcus?
He's staying for the earthquake?

09:35.885 --> 09:39.320
Oh, I can't wait! I am
all about the earthquake.

09:39.360 --> 09:40.570
If it's too real for you,

09:40.610 --> 09:43.120
by all means, scamper off
out of here... Greg.

09:44.080 --> 09:45.269
You are really staying with him?

09:50.419 --> 09:53.179
OK. Safe trip, then. Off you pop.

09:53.253 --> 09:55.240
- Bon voyage.
- Hey, on.

09:56.789 --> 09:58.830
They are so pathetic.
Well,

09:59.145 --> 10:01.779
these things really separate
the men from the boys, don't they?

10:01.820 --> 10:05.129
And on the plus side, we've got
the whole place to ourselves.

10:13.879 --> 10:15.690
Hey, Strabo.

10:15.730 --> 10:17.730
Terrific forecast, earlier.

10:17.769 --> 10:19.519
Please pass on my thanks
to the ants.

10:19.559 --> 10:22.309
Yes, will do.
Are you going somewhere?

10:22.350 --> 10:24.460
Mm... I thought I'd go and stay
with my sister.

10:24.500 --> 10:28.289
Yes, my reading for tomorrow's
changed somewhat, you see?

10:28.330 --> 10:30.639
Oh, right. What's going on?
There is still a tremor?

10:30.679 --> 10:33.889
Oh, yes, but it may be a bit bigger.
Bigger?

10:33.899 --> 10:34.820
How much bigger?

10:34.830 --> 10:38.625
Well, I checked with the ants and
they were quite, well... antsy.

10:38.673 --> 10:40.850
They are now suggesting
a full-blown earthquake...

10:40.889 --> 10:42.519
but I'm sure
it will be fine, though.

10:42.559 --> 10:45.399
What? No, you're not.
You're gonna stay with your sister.

10:45.692 --> 10:47.429
Yes, that is true.

10:47.799 --> 10:51.159
The ants can be wrong, of course.
So it could be nothing, then?

10:51.200 --> 10:53.206
Oh, absolutely. It could be nothing.

11:00.832 --> 11:01.893
Excuse me.

11:05.232 --> 11:08.232
You're completely overreacting,
the guy's a gibbering looney.

11:08.285 --> 11:10.509
- He's a respected weatherist...
- Who talks to ants!

11:10.549 --> 11:11.529
He knows his stuff.

11:11.539 --> 11:14.306
Yesterday, he said it would be
overcast with sunny spells.

11:14.360 --> 11:18.212
- And Io...it was!
- That's not Io, that's default forecast.

11:18.225 --> 11:20.346
He could have just said,
"There'll be weather".

11:20.385 --> 11:24.000
I trust him. He said curry
were nice and it is... very nice.

11:24.039 --> 11:26.120
I wouldn't be surprised if there's
a monster quake on the way.

11:26.159 --> 11:28.245
Oh... so presumably you'll
wanna get out of town, then.

11:28.306 --> 11:31.706
Nah, sounds like a right faff.
Uh-huh? What about you, then?

11:31.765 --> 11:33.812
Oh, no, I've got to hunker down
with Pandora.

11:33.852 --> 11:36.600
This might be the only time
she can... slot me in.

11:36.665 --> 11:39.200
I figured you might prioritise
slotting yourself in over survival.

11:39.240 --> 11:41.500
Well, at least I'll die happy, Marcus.

11:41.519 --> 11:43.279
- Come on, we're gonna be late for work.
- What?!

11:43.312 --> 11:45.840
I'm not going to work.
There's gonna be an earthquake!

11:45.885 --> 11:47.370
Whatever!
See you tonight, then.

11:47.409 --> 11:51.100
I sincerely hope so.
Yeah, I'll see you tonight!

