12:03.686 --> 12:04.700
Morning, Shredder.

12:04.725 --> 12:06.460
Oh, hey. Where is everyone?

12:06.500 --> 12:08.529
Good question. No-one seems
to have shown up.

12:08.570 --> 12:10.200
That's weird.
Isn't it?

12:10.240 --> 12:13.059
One wonders if it has anything to do
with the memo you sent yesterday

12:13.110 --> 12:15.086
informing them there'd be
an earthquake?

12:15.120 --> 12:19.024
Well, no, that was meant as an
invitation, not a out-vitation.

12:19.025 --> 12:22.066
Well, your out-vitation has lost me
my whole staff.

12:22.090 --> 12:23.179
Not your whole staff!
No.

12:23.320 --> 12:26.320
No, a few of the keenest beans
and saddest sacks

12:26.360 --> 12:27.580
have decided to brave it.

12:27.620 --> 12:30.019
Morning, guys.
Oh, great! Hey, morning, Pandora.

12:30.059 --> 12:31.269
So sorry that I'm late,

12:31.286 --> 12:33.840
but I've been at a breakfasting
network event.

12:33.879 --> 12:37.232
Have a terrific day.
Yeah, let's really make it count.

12:37.686 --> 12:40.750
I hope for your sake there's a
catastrophic earthquake, Shredder,

12:40.779 --> 12:43.419
or you are so fired!

12:43.840 --> 12:45.840
OK. Fingers crossed.

12:48.546 --> 12:50.149
What can I get you, gentlemen?

12:50.190 --> 12:52.980
And I'm afraid I still won't be able
to serve you the red curry.

12:53.019 --> 12:55.009
Yeah, that's fine,
we're not hungry today.

12:55.049 --> 12:58.159
We just thought we'd come by to
let you know about the earthquake.

12:59.265 --> 13:00.100
The what?

13:00.186 --> 13:03.265
Any minute now. Gonna squash
the lot, apparently.

13:05.033 --> 13:06.500
Here they come.

13:06.732 --> 13:08.905
We are in bloody business here.

13:15.110 --> 13:17.100
Move it!

13:17.946 --> 13:19.505
This is so annoying.

13:19.539 --> 13:23.740
- We still need candles, rope, bandages.
- Bandages?

13:23.750 --> 13:26.145
Definitely?
And everyone's closing!

13:26.173 --> 13:27.269
Look!

13:27.472 --> 13:31.679
Hey, I was thinking, why don't we
do something crazy and spontaneous?

13:31.720 --> 13:33.552
Sure, OK, great. Like what?

13:33.566 --> 13:36.653
Like, I dunno... go to Tuscany
for a mini-break?

13:36.673 --> 13:39.452
It doesn't sound that crazy.
But it would be spontaneous...

13:39.490 --> 13:42.480
if we go now, jump in a cart
and just head for the hills!

13:42.519 --> 13:46.046
But then we'd miss the earthquake?
Oh, yeah, I guess we would!

13:46.092 --> 13:48.352
And you are all about
the earthquake, right?

13:48.393 --> 13:49.732
Yeah, course.

13:49.820 --> 13:52.090
I'd just rather be all about it
from Tuscany.

13:52.129 --> 13:54.759
We can go afterwards if we
are still up for it, then.

13:54.773 --> 13:56.950
And I guess... alive?

13:57.620 --> 13:59.389
I'll pick up the bandages
and the rope.

13:59.613 --> 14:01.605
You go and get some candles
from your place.

14:01.633 --> 14:03.039
And then we'll meet back at mine.

14:03.092 --> 14:07.039
And hurry... this could be
a once-in-a-lifetime thing.

14:07.080 --> 14:08.909
Yeah, I know.

14:09.909 --> 14:11.710
It could well be.

14:17.980 --> 14:19.639
Where are you, you red bastard?

14:21.120 --> 14:23.200
Bingo.
Are you sure?

14:23.265 --> 14:25.340
Oh, yeah. Nearly took my schnozz off!

14:25.379 --> 14:26.779
Mmm.

14:27.052 --> 14:31.586
Oh, praise Jupiter... and of course,
the Indian God of lovely grub.

14:31.645 --> 14:33.159
Amen.

14:37.326 --> 14:38.820
Haw... haw... haw.

14:38.860 --> 14:40.809
Is it hot?

14:40.850 --> 14:42.879
Hot... hot.

14:43.580 --> 14:45.100
Norks alive!

14:45.165 --> 14:48.605
I don't think I can take it.
Don't let it beat you, big boy.

14:48.653 --> 14:51.860
Come on, chew through the pain!
Ow! Ooh, mamma!

14:51.932 --> 14:54.379
Ooh, mamma. Mamma.

15:01.105 --> 15:03.253
It's only Marcus!
All right, landlord.

15:03.312 --> 15:05.090
Got any plans for this "earthquake"?

15:05.129 --> 15:06.600
Yeah, I think I might die in it.

15:06.653 --> 15:08.960
Oh, fair do's.
I'm getting out of here.

15:09.000 --> 15:12.245
Between you and me, I built
this place on the cheap.

15:12.273 --> 15:15.466
No, what a surprise
A fruity fart could blow it down.

15:15.500 --> 15:18.409
Right, well... make sure they put
something appropriate on my grave.

15:18.450 --> 15:20.686
Like, "Here lies
a fucking bell-end."

15:20.745 --> 15:23.559
No problem. Oh, you've not
seen Davus, have you?

15:23.666 --> 15:25.580
I saved him a seat
in the cart.

15:25.633 --> 15:28.405
No. I suppose you'll have to go
without the big bozo.

15:28.432 --> 15:29.970
You don't want it, do you?

15:30.826 --> 15:32.765
25 dinari each way.

15:32.799 --> 15:36.326
50 for priority boarding
or any luggage over three kilos.

15:36.352 --> 15:38.773
Sorry, I had to squeeze one out.

15:38.826 --> 15:40.700
I don't like shitting by the road.

15:40.725 --> 15:42.993
Course not, you're a lady.

15:43.846 --> 15:45.720
Are you coming, then?

15:51.385 --> 15:52.820
Thanks so much for coming.

15:53.046 --> 15:54.566
Do you want to take off
your coat, maybe?

15:54.639 --> 15:57.926
Er... I won't. I'm just putting in
face time, can't hunker long.

15:57.966 --> 16:00.860
Of course. Would you like a glass
of water while you're here?

16:00.893 --> 16:02.059
Thank you, I would.

16:02.100 --> 16:04.832
Aurelius?
I'm not helping you out, mate.

16:04.893 --> 16:06.566
Come on, it's your job.

16:06.832 --> 16:08.139
OK, but only for her.

16:08.179 --> 16:12.253
So what's the gameplan here?
I guess we just hunker and wait.

16:12.279 --> 16:13.385
Ah, because I should flag up

16:13.426 --> 16:16.225
that I do have a basket weaving
class starting imminently.

16:16.253 --> 16:17.970
Yeah, it should be here any sec.

16:20.639 --> 16:23.192
Er... have you been in any other
natural disasters?

16:23.232 --> 16:25.092
Erm...let me think...

16:25.200 --> 16:27.100
not a disaster as such,

16:27.139 --> 16:29.926
but we were snowed in
when I was a child and...

16:29.946 --> 16:31.950
We couldn't open the door
because of all the snow.

16:31.990 --> 16:35.245
- Wow. So what happened?
- It melted, presumably.

16:35.265 --> 16:36.929
Er... stay out of this, please.

16:37.173 --> 16:39.519
Did it?
It did, yes.

16:40.159 --> 16:42.580
I'm sorry, but I'm gonna have to
duck out now, guys.

16:42.605 --> 16:45.192
Wait... I think I can feel it coming!

16:45.332 --> 16:47.139
Holy Jove, can you feel it?

16:47.192 --> 16:47.893
No.

16:47.894 --> 16:50.513
Yeah, I'm really not getting
any vibes on this one.

16:50.539 --> 16:53.980
Look, forget basket weaving.
I can't. We're doing handles today.

16:54.005 --> 16:56.485
There's an earthquake coming!
And I wish the timing was better

16:56.505 --> 16:58.740
but I really can't
squeeze it in right now.

16:58.779 --> 17:00.769
Thanks again for the water.

17:20.759 --> 17:22.579
Oh!
Oh, oh, oh...

17:22.618 --> 17:24.380
Hot!

17:24.420 --> 17:26.410
Oh!

17:28.553 --> 17:29.506
Did you hear that?

17:29.539 --> 17:31.750
I can't hear shit,
all my senses are numb.

17:31.789 --> 17:33.589
There was a rumble.
Probably my tummy.

17:33.732 --> 17:36.099
No, no. It was bigger than that.
Your tummy?

17:36.140 --> 17:37.579
I think it was the earthquake.

17:37.653 --> 17:39.809
Hmm... sweet.

17:42.039 --> 17:43.925
Ah, bollocks.

17:44.113 --> 17:46.032
I'd better go and find
the wife and kid really.

17:46.066 --> 17:48.826
My missus will be well angry
if she dies and I'm not there.

17:48.880 --> 17:50.653
Right... I reckon I'll press on.

17:50.712 --> 17:53.579
Well, have a good quake.
Better catch you, big lad.

17:55.726 --> 17:56.789
Hot!

18:00.480 --> 18:01.700
Shredder?

18:02.740 --> 18:04.432
You're still here, I see.

18:04.509 --> 18:06.885
Well, you know, I take my job
very seriously.

18:06.913 --> 18:09.292
Yes, of course.
Hence inventing an earthquake

18:09.319 --> 18:12.006
in order to lure co-workers
to a panicky fuck-fest!

18:12.086 --> 18:13.692
I didn't invent it, exactly.

18:13.759 --> 18:16.605
No? Then where did this rumour
of yours come from?

18:16.685 --> 18:18.480
And make this good
or you will lose your job.

18:18.526 --> 18:21.730
Well, my neighbour's got these ants
that know the future.

18:21.769 --> 18:23.569
And you're fired!
Here is your contract,

18:23.609 --> 18:26.079
if you'd like to perform
your final act of shredding.

18:26.400 --> 18:28.109
I...

18:31.299 --> 18:33.210
Ants indeed!

18:33.250 --> 18:35.450
I've never heard anything
so preposterous.

18:35.490 --> 18:37.759
Yeah, I know! The guy's a crackpot!

18:37.799 --> 18:40.869
I think I might hunker down here,
just in case.

18:41.220 --> 18:42.980
Mmm... I think I might join you.

19:00.960 --> 19:03.240
Here it comes. Brace yourselves.

19:05.566 --> 19:06.730
God!
Whoa!

19:06.740 --> 19:09.766
Urgh! Get off me, you pervert.

19:12.809 --> 19:13.799
You all right, Mum?

19:13.819 --> 19:16.829
Huh! This beaky bastard
tried to molest me.

19:16.869 --> 19:18.869
I didn't.
It was the quake, it...

19:19.252 --> 19:20.380
Hang on, has it finished?

19:20.413 --> 19:23.329
Yeah. I'll turn her around.

19:23.369 --> 19:25.359
That was the earthquake?

19:25.400 --> 19:27.640
What a load of rubbish.

19:30.573 --> 19:33.519
Back we go. No refunds.

19:39.692 --> 19:41.726
I expected that to last longer.

19:41.766 --> 19:42.952
Sorry, it usually does.

19:43.019 --> 19:46.026
I meant the earthquake!
Oh, yeah, of course.

19:46.220 --> 19:47.529
Thought it would be bigger.

19:47.569 --> 19:49.046
Erm... the earthquake again?

19:49.066 --> 19:51.685
Yes. Although the earth
didn't really move

19:51.700 --> 19:53.950
in either regard,
to be honest, Shredder.

19:57.333 --> 19:59.605
So not like that
was payment or anything,

19:59.645 --> 20:01.553
but could I have
my job back now, please?

20:01.579 --> 20:02.432
- You may...
- Yes!

20:02.433 --> 20:04.712
...provided you never breathe
a word of this to anyone

20:04.732 --> 20:05.792
as long as you live.

20:05.859 --> 20:08.846
Oh, yeah, obviously.
What?! What do you mean, obviously?

20:08.873 --> 20:10.819
Oh, nothing, I just...

20:10.980 --> 20:13.766
my lips are sealed. Good.
Now get out!

20:14.119 --> 20:16.049
Same time next earthquake?
Out!

20:16.086 --> 20:17.589
OK, yeah

20:27.880 --> 20:29.553
Hey. So sorry.

20:29.566 --> 20:31.349
It took ages to find my candles.

20:31.390 --> 20:34.826
And then I got trapped
under a sort of... beam!

20:34.865 --> 20:38.313
Uh-huh? Was it before or after
you got a lift out of town?

20:38.353 --> 20:40.559
I... Sorry, what?

20:40.593 --> 20:43.726
I saw you in the cart.
You sneaky little rat.

20:43.779 --> 20:45.972
Um... Right.

20:46.059 --> 20:47.865
What's that shit on your tunic?

20:47.920 --> 20:50.752
Er... it's supposed to be rubble.

20:50.813 --> 20:53.859
Hey, Marcus.
What's he doing here?

20:53.900 --> 20:55.326
And also in a towel?

20:55.373 --> 20:58.119
Where were you, man?
You missed our little party.

20:58.165 --> 21:00.232
What? Did you..?

21:00.640 --> 21:01.425
With him?

21:01.480 --> 21:04.653
There was an earthquake. We thought
we were going to die.

21:04.680 --> 21:07.492
And you were supposed to be out
of town, you Gallic git.

21:07.526 --> 21:08.869
I came back.

21:08.910 --> 21:11.700
It's times like this where you
realise who you care about most.

21:15.880 --> 21:18.952
She wasn't the Gaul for you.
I've always said that.

21:19.000 --> 21:21.486
You like mini-breaks,
she likes earthquakes.

21:21.566 --> 21:23.486
Yeah... how was the office, then?

21:23.519 --> 21:25.212
Did you manage to "hunker down"?

21:25.259 --> 21:27.752
Uh-huh. Yeah, it wasn't quite
what I had in mind,

21:27.772 --> 21:29.400
but I did do some hunkering.

21:29.465 --> 21:32.049
Well, at least things worked out
for one of us.

21:32.089 --> 21:34.089
Er...
Hey up? Look who it is?

21:34.130 --> 21:36.440
Oi! So much for
your giant earthquake.

21:36.665 --> 21:38.266
Oh, yes, I know.

21:38.286 --> 21:40.766
The ants pass on their
profound apologies.

21:40.786 --> 21:44.413
Some of their predictions
are built on shaky ground,

21:44.425 --> 21:45.819
as it were.

21:45.873 --> 21:50.880
Oh, look, it's starting to rain!
They did get one thing right.

21:51.869 --> 21:54.700
Yeah, great, because things weren't
shit enough already!

21:54.740 --> 21:58.932
Hey up, that's not rain, mate.
That's snow!

21:58.986 --> 22:00.480
Yes!
Ha!

22:00.519 --> 22:03.819
It's snowing!
See... things couldn't be any better.

22:05.346 --> 22:06.700
Hey!

22:16.726 --> 22:18.099
Boom!

22:19.900 --> 22:21.490
All right. Er... Grumio!

